# Page folder structure

The app is a Next.js App Router project deployed on a server (Vercel). The App
Router lives in `src/app/` (with `src/middleware.ts` and
`src/instrumentation-client.ts`). Routing is **file-based** under
`src/app/[lang]/**`: each route has a `page.tsx` that exports
`generateStaticParams` (pre-renders both locales), `generateMetadata` (per-page
SEO via `@/i18n/seo-meta`), and `export const dynamicParams = false`.
`src/middleware.ts` keeps English at the root (no prefix) and Vietnamese under
`/vi` by rewriting `/x` -> `/en/x` internally.

## Where view code lives (colocation - IMPORTANT)

The page VIEW code lives IN the route folder, not in a separate `src/features/`
tree:

- **Server Component pages** (static, presentational: home, hubs) inline the view
  directly in `page.tsx` (`async` component, translations via
  `getTranslations`/`getLocale` from `next-intl/server`; prime the locale with
  `primePageLocale(params)` from `@/i18n/server` so SSG is preserved).
- **Client Component pages** (interactive: quizzes, charts, writing, lessons) put
  the view in a colocated `_components/` folder next to `page.tsx` (Next treats
  `_`-prefixed folders as private / non-routable). `page.tsx` (server) imports it
  via `./_components/<name>.tsx` and wraps interactive views in `<ClientOnly>`.
- **Page-specific** helpers/sub-components go in that route's `_components/` too
  (same-folder `./` imports).
- **Shared internal clusters** (used by sibling routes: `course/choice-button`,
  `course/shared`, the whole `alphabet/exercise/*` helper set) stay in
  `src/features/<feature>/` and are imported via the `@/features/...` alias. They
  live here (not in `app/_components`) because the ESLint `no-restricted-imports`
  ban on `../` makes cross-route colocated imports impractical (`@/app/[lang]/...`
  is ugly), and non-app code (constants, scripts) must not depend on `app/`.
- **Globally reusable UI** stays in `src/components/<name>/index.tsx`; shared
  data/logic imported by non-app code stays in `src/constants` / `src/utils`
  (e.g. `src/constants/gojuon.ts`, `src/components/alphabet-chart`).

Views read route params via `useParams` from `@/i18n/navigation`.

## Locale prefix + hydration (IMPORTANT gotcha, cost a prod outage)

At build/SSR time English pages render under the INTERNAL `/en/...` path (the
middleware rewrite), but on the client the URL is the clean `/x`. So any RENDERED
output derived from `usePathname()`/`useLocation().pathname` (active-nav
`selected` state, expanded groups, links) MUST normalize via `stripLocalePrefix`,
and `stripLocalePrefix` MUST strip BOTH `/en` and `/vi` (not just `/vi`). If it
leaves `/en` in place, SSR output differs from the client and React throws a
hydration mismatch (#418) that - via the global `window 'error'` listener in
`ErrorBoundary` - trips the error fallback on EVERY non-home English page (home
has no matching nav group so it slips through). This ONLY reproduces in a
PRODUCTION build (`next build` prerenders at `/en/...`), never in `next dev` - so
validate page health against a prod build, not dev.

CAVEAT: `ErrorBoundary` (`src/components/error-boundary`) also attaches a GLOBAL
`window 'error'` / `unhandledrejection` listener, so ANY uncaught error on the
page (even one React would recover from) flips it to the full-screen fallback.
This is what amplified the small hydration mismatch above into every English page
showing the fallback. Keep this in mind when debugging "whole page is the error
screen"; a future improvement is to make the boundary rely on
`getDerivedStateFromError`/`componentDidCatch` instead of the broad global listener.

## "Every page works" testing

- The CI `build` job (`pnpm build`) prerenders all ~1,400 pages and fails on any
  render error - that is the exhaustive server-render guarantee.
- `e2e/pages-smoke.spec.ts` covers ONE rich example per page TYPE in both locales
  (not every page - same type shares one component) and checks health with 5
  signals: status < 400, no uncaught `pageerror` (catches hydration mismatches),
  no same-origin 5xx (broken chunk), a real `<h1>` in `<main>`, and NO error
  boundary (via `data-testid="error-boundary"` on `ErrorFallback` - not localized
  text, since the fallback ALSO renders an `<h1>`). A sitemap self-check test
  fails if a new route type has no example; a control test triggers `/sentry-test`
  to prove the boundary DOES appear on error.
- E2E runs against a PRODUCTION build in CI / with `E2E_PROD=1` (dev has
  on-demand-compile flakiness -> transient 500s). `E2E_PORT` reuses a running
  server. When a new route TYPE is added, add it to `REPRESENTATIVE_PAGES`.

## Mapping (view code lives in the route folder)

| Route | View |
|-------|------|
| `/`, `/alphabet`, `/alphabet/exercise`, `/kanji` | inlined in that route's `page.tsx` (Server Component) |
| `/alphabet/hiragana` | `src/app/[lang]/alphabet/hiragana/_components/hiragana-chart.tsx` |
| `/alphabet/katakana` | `.../alphabet/katakana/_components/katakana-chart.tsx` |
| `/alphabet/combined` | `.../alphabet/combined/_components/combined-chart.tsx` |
| `/alphabet/exercise/<kind>` | `.../alphabet/exercise/<kind>/_components/<kind>-exercise.tsx` |
| `/:level` | `src/app/[lang]/[jlptLevel]/_components/course-page.tsx` |
| `/:level/:lessonId` | `.../[jlptLevel]/[lessonId]/_components/lesson-page.tsx` |
| `/:level/:lessonId/vocabulary` | `.../[lessonId]/vocabulary/_components/exercise-page.tsx` |
| `/:level/:lessonId/{grammar,listening,reading,writing}` | `.../[lessonId]/<kind>/_components/<kind>-page.tsx` |
| `/kanji/:track` | `src/app/[lang]/kanji/[track]/_components/kanji-track.tsx` |
| `/kanji/:track/:lessonId(/quiz/writing)` | `.../[lessonId](/quiz/writing)/_components/kanji-*.tsx` |
| `/kanji/radicals` | `.../kanji/radicals/_components/kanji-radicals.tsx` |

Page-specific quiz logic is colocated in the same `_components/` folder (e.g.
`vocabulary/_components/vocab-quiz.ts`, `grammar/_components/grammar-quiz.ts`,
`listening/_components/course-listening.ts`), imported via `./`. Course views
read `[jlptLevel]`/`[lessonId]` via `useParams`.

## Navigation & params (Next, not react-router)

- There is NO `react-router-dom`. Client navigation uses `next/link` (wrapped by
  `LocaleLink`/`LocaleNavLink` in `@/components/locale-link`, which prefix the
  active locale) and the shim hooks in `@/i18n/navigation` (`useParams`,
  `usePathname`, `useLocation`, `useNavigate`). Import route params/pathname from
  `@/i18n/navigation`, never from `react-router-dom`.

## Shared components / folders (IMPORTANT)

- Globally reusable UI lives in its own folder as `src/components/<name>/index.tsx`, imported extensionless: `import { SpeakButton } from '@/components/speak-button'`. Do NOT keep multiple sibling components as flat files in one folder.
- A page's own view + helpers live in that route's `_components/` (or inline in `page.tsx` for Server Components).
- A shared internal cluster (used by sibling routes) stays in `src/features/<feature>/` and is imported via `@/features/...` (e.g. `@/components`-style folders `course/choice-button`, `course/shared`, plus the flat `alphabet/exercise/*` helper set).
- Shared data/logic imported by non-app code (constants, scripts) lives in `src/constants` / `src/utils` (e.g. `src/constants/gojuon.ts`), never inside `app/`.
- Colocate a `*.test.ts(x)` next to the file it tests.

## New pages

When adding a route `/foo/bar`, create `src/app/[lang]/foo/bar/page.tsx` (server:
`generateStaticParams` + `generateMetadata` + `export const dynamicParams = false`).
Then either inline the view in `page.tsx` (Server Component - static content,
translate via `getTranslations` + `primePageLocale(params)`), or put an
interactive view in `./_components/<name>.tsx` (`'use client'`) and render it
(wrap in `<ClientOnly>` if it reads browser state / picks random questions).
Register the logical path in `src/constants/routes.ts` (or a `*_SITEMAP_PATHS`
array) so `app/sitemap.ts` includes it. Add param-generation helpers in
`@/i18n/route-helpers` when the route has dynamic segments.

## Imports

- `./...` for same-folder siblings and this route's `_components/` (e.g. `./_components/foo.tsx`).
- `@/...` alias for everything else (`@/components/...`, `@/features/...`, `@/constants/...`). NEVER use `../` (ESLint `no-restricted-imports` forbids it), so cross-route sharing must go through `src/` (aliased), not a sibling route's `_components/`.
